I"<h3 id="using-ucscs-high-performance-computational-cluster-hummingbird">Using UCSC’s high-performance computational cluster (Hummingbird)</h3>

<ul>
  <li>There are lots of resources available at <a href="https://www.hb.ucsc.edu">hb.ucsc.edu</a>.</li>
  <li>You can find the slides from the s/lab presentation <a href="/assets/documents/jwv_slab_hb.pdf">here</a>, and a sample SLURM and R script below (which you can also download by clicking the links below.)</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="sample-slurm-script-download-with-comments">Sample SLURM script (<a href="/assets/documents/job.slurm">download with comments</a>)</h4>

<p class="code">#!/bin/bash\<br />
#SBATCH –nodes=1<br />
#SBATCH –partition=128x24<br />
#SBATCH –job-name=my_job<br />
#SBATCH –mail-type=ALL<br />
#SBATCH –mail-user=[your_user_name]@ucsc.edu<br />
#SBATCH –ntasks=1<br />
#SBATCH –output=%j.out<br />
#SBATCH –error=%j.err<br />
module load R/R-3.5.0<br />
R –no-save &lt; script.R</p>

<h4 id="sample-r-script-that-saves-an-object-as-an-rds-file-that-you-can-download-download-with-comments">Sample R script that saves an object as an RDS file that you can download [<a href="documents/script.R">download with comments</a>]</h4>

<p class="code">r_object &lt;- 1*1<br />
saveRDS(r_object, file = “test.rds”)</p>
